"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777701","Cabinet Office","false","2017-10-30","<p>The current boundary review is proceeding in accordance with legislation passed in the 2010-15 Parliament under which all four Boundary Commissions, including the Boundary Commission for England, are required to submit their final reports in September 2018.</p><p>These reforms will ensure fair and equal representation for the voting public across the United Kingdom.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-10-30T15:45:21.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777701/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777701/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777701/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-25","Constituencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the Government plans to bring forward the recommendations of the proposed Boundary Review 2018 in England.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","109636"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777702","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-11-03","<p>I refer the Hon member to my answer to PQ 108123.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","109965","2017-11-03T09:43:10.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777702/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777702/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777702/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2017-10-25","Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 25 October 2017 to Question 108122, on cybercrime, how many registered consultancies of the Government's Cyber Essentials scheme had data exposed.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","109582"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777703","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-16","<p>Information regarding the total number of unregistered people of voting age is not held by the Government. Only totals for the number of registered electors are held, and these can be accessed through the Office For National Statistics website.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-11-16T16:08:55.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777703/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777703/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777703/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-25","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many and what proportion of adults of voting age were not registered to vote in each year from 2010 to date.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","109585"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777704","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-14","<p>Forecasts for Brexit-related costs are embedded in the Cabinet Office’s budget.</p>","Ashford","Damian Green",,"2017-11-14T10:41:03.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777704/answer","Biography information for Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777704/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777704/answer","Ashford","Damian Green","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777704/answer/previousversion/18498","Biography information for Damian Green","53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-25","Cabinet Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what contingency funding his Department has allocated in relation to the Government's negotiations on the UK leaving the EU for the (a) 2017-18, (b) 2018-19 and (c) 2019-20 financial years.","false","Biography information for Stella Creasy","Walthamstow","Stella Creasy","109779"
