"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777744","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-30","<p>As has been announced previously all our Astute Class submarines will be based at Her Majesty's Naval Base Clyde.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-30T16:24:24.963Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777744/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777744/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777744/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Astute Class Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the base-porting arrangements are for the most recent Astute-class attack submarine.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","109632"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777745","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-01","<p>The Hawk T1 fleet has undergone various upgrade and life extension programmes since delivery. The out-of-service date has been calculated with regards to the usual fleet management processes in place on the large remaining fleet of Hawk T1.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-01T15:25:52.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777745/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777745/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777745/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Hawk Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons the decision to extend the out-of-service date for the Hawk T1 aircraft was made.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","109555"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777746","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-02","<p>The Government is carrying out an ongoing programme of comprehensive analytical work that will inform our negotiating position with the EU, to define our deep and special partnership with the EU and inform our understanding of how EU exit will affect the UK's domestic policies and frameworks. The Ministry of Defence is working with officials across Government, in close coordination with the Department for Exiting the European Union, to ensure the delivery of a holistic programme of analysis.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-11-02T16:14:31.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777746/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777746/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777746/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Ministry of Defence: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department was consulted by the Department for Exiting the European Union on the economic impact assessments conducted for the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","109531"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777747","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-30","<p>The UK will undertake maintenance of the F-35 aircraft at RAF Marham when the aircraft arrives in 2018. In the event that any maintenance is required which cannot be conducted at RAF Marham then this will be conducted at one of a number of locations around the world as part of the Global Support Solution.</p><p>Defence Electronics and Components Agency Sealand has been chosen by the F-35 Joint Programme Office as the global repair hub for avionic and aircraft components for all F-35 Lightning aircraft.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-30T16:19:48.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777747/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777747/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777747/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, where the maintenance of the F-35B aircraft will take place.","false","Biography information for Wayne David","Caerphilly","Wayne David","109683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777748","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-03","<p>The number of Army personnel at Maindy Barracks in the years requested is shown below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>As at</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Strength</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2014</p></td><td><p>300</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2015</p></td><td><p>370</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2016</p></td><td><p>420</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Numbers have been rounded to 10 in accordance with disclosure control and rounding policy, numbers ending in &quot;5&quot; have been rounded to the nearest multiple of 20 to prevent systematic bias.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-11-03T14:01:55.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777748/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777748/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777748/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Maindy Barracks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many service personnel were based at Maindy Barracks in (a) 2014, (b) 2015 and (c) 2016.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","109600"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777749","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-02","<p>As set out in the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review, the UK is intending to procure 138 F-35 aircraft over the life of the programme.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-02T16:15:16.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777749/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777749/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777749/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether it is the Government's policy to purchase 138 F35 aircraft.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","109656"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777750","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-02","<p>The costs of F-35 spares, software upgrades, and logistic support are included within the Department's financial planning assumptions for the F-35 programme. The F-35 Joint Program Office procures all of these elements on behalf the F-35 Partner Nations.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-02T16:13:48.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777750/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777750/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777750/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what financial assumptions his Department has made on the cost of (a) spare parts, (b) software upgrades and (c) logistics support for the F-35 programme; and whether those costs are borne by his Department or the supplier for that programme.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","109657"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777751","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-02","<p>The latest contract price is $241,579 per Generation III helmet.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-02T16:23:00.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777751/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777751/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777751/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the unit cost is of the Generation III helmets being procured for pilots of the Lockheed Martin F-35 fighter jets.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","109658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777752","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-02","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) centrally manages the impact of variations in foreign exchange rates as part of the routine financial management of the defence programme. The foreign currency arrangements in place will limit any impact from the current foreign exchange position and any further considerations will be dealt with as part of the MOD's annual planning cycle.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-02T16:16:03.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777752/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777752/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777752/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to manage exposure to foreign currency fluctuations as part of his Department's F-35 programme.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","109659"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777753","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-02","<p>The F-35 Joint Program Office is managing the procurement of the Automomic logistics Information System (ALIS) on behalf of the F-35 Partner Nations. The ALIS system is still within its development test phase and any software issues that are discovered are rectified as part of the development process.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-02T16:23:38.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777753/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777753/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777753/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to ensure that software bugs identified in the Autonomic Logistics Information System on the F-35 aircraft are remedied.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","109660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777754","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-01","<p>We are buying sufficient numbers of F-35B aircraft to meet our requirements. A decision on whether or not to acquire replacement aircraft would be taken in the light of circumstances at the time.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-01T15:25:07.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777754/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777754/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777754/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what contingency or replacement policy his Department has in place if any F-35 variant is lost during operations.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","109661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777755","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-30","<p>The Ministry of Defence has worked closely across Government to identify costs that would arise from any necessary contingency action. These costs have been scoped but the Department has not yet needed to commit any expenditure.</p><p>The evolution and complexity of the challenges facing us require the UK and EU to continue to collaborate closely in foreign policy, defence and development - to uphold and project our shared values, combat our shared threats, and promote our mutual prosperity.</p><p>The Government therefore remains confident a deal will be struck and this funding will not be required.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","109781","2017-10-30T16:22:28.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777755/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777755/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777755/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Ministry of Defence: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what contingency funding his Department has allocated in relation to the Government's negotiations on the UK leaving the EU for the (a) current, (b) 2018-19 and (c) 2019-20 financial year.","false","Biography information for Stella Creasy","Walthamstow","Stella Creasy","109776"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777756","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-30","<p>On current plans, the out of service date for HMS SCOTT is 2022.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-30T16:23:01.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777756/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777756/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777756/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","HMS Scott","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the current planned operational retirement date is for HMS Scott.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","109631"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777757","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-30","<p>The Secretary of State for Defence Policy Statement for Health, Safety and Environmental Protection requires that all organisations across Defence comply with the relevant statutory requirements that includes the Regulatory Reform (Fire Safety) Order 2005 (FSO).</p><p>The assessment of compliance with the FSO is the responsibility of the Director General Defence Safety Authority (DG DSA) who operates under a Charter from the Secretary of State for Defence. This assessment is undertaken by the DSA Defence Fire Safety Regulator (DFSR) who as the enforcing authority for the FSO undertakes a programme of risk based audits of Defence-occupied premises to verify compliance with UK fire safety legislation.</p><p>The DFSR audit process includes an assessment of the level of compliance against all the relevant articles in the FSO that include those relating to fire safety arrangements and the procedures in place to provide appropriate evacuation drills to follow in cases of serious and imminent danger to persons.</p><p>In addition to allocating assurance levels across each Regulatory Domain and to reflect the importance attached to this issue, DG DSA raised fire safety as a strategic risk in his 2016/17 Annual Assurance Report that will shortly be published at:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dsa-annual-assurance-reports</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-30T16:50:38.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777757/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777757/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777757/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Military Bases: Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the Regulatory Reform (Fire Safety) Order 2005 in ensuring that (a) adequate fire safety arrangements and (b) appropriate fire drills, including evacuations, are carried out for military bases in the UK.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","109676"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777758","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-02","<p>The Department is in regular discussions with the US Government-led F-35 Joint Program Office, which manages the programme on behalf of the F-35 Partner Nations, and with Lockheed Martin, the aircraft production integrator, to ensure contracted production targets are met.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-02T16:12:14.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777758/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777758/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777758/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent discussions officials of his Department have had with (a) their counterparts in the US Administration or (b) representatives of Lockheed Martin on production targets for the F35 variants falling behind schedule.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","109736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777759","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-02","<p>The F-35 Joint Program Office (JPO) procures F-35 aircraft on behalf of all the F-35 Partner Nations. All of the aircraft to be procured in production lots 12, 13 and 14 are currently in the costing and negotiation phase. Our expectation is to see cost reduction with each successive production lot. Cost reduction targets are not released in advance as to do so could undermine the JPO's negotiations with industry.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-02T16:13:16.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777759/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777759/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777759/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent discussions officials of his Department have had with (a) their counterparts in the US Administration or (b) representatives of Lockheed Martin on cost reduction targets for the UK F35 variants in production batches 12, 13 and 14.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","109737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777760","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-30","<p>The Ministry of Defence has worked closely across Government to identify costs that would arise from any necessary contingency action. These costs have been scoped but the Department has not yet needed to commit any expenditure.</p><p>The evolution and complexity of the challenges facing us require the UK and EU to continue to collaborate closely in foreign policy, defence and development - to uphold and project our shared values, combat our shared threats, and promote our mutual prosperity.</p><p>The Government therefore remains confident a deal will be struck and this funding will not be required.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","109776","2017-10-30T16:22:28.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777760/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777760/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777760/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-25","Ministry of Defence: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what funding his Department has set aside for contingencies relating to the UK leaving the EU in the (a) current and (b) 2018-19 financial year.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","109781"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777761","Department for Education","false","2017-11-03","<p>This information is not available in the format requested.</p><p>The Higher Education Statistics Authority (HESA) is responsible for collecting and publishing official statistics on the sources of income that each university receives. This is collected retrospectively and so the latest year that financial data is available for is 2015/16. Aggregate data for the sector can be viewed here: <a href="https://www.hesa.ac.uk/data-and-analysis/publications/finances-2015-16/introduction" target="_blank">https://www.hesa.ac.uk/data-and-analysis/publications/finances-2015-16/introduction</a>.</p><p>Information for the 2017/18 academic year will be published by HESA in spring 2019.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-11-03T14:12:40.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777761/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777761/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777761/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Universities: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the average contribution from the public purse to each Russell Group university is for 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","109692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777762","Department for Education","false","2017-11-03","<p>The Government takes the safety of pupils and teachers very seriously. All schools have to follow strict fire safety regulations, including having a Fire Risk Assessment, designed to ensure they are as safe as possible and well prepared in the event of a fire.</p><p>All new school building projects must comply with Building Regulations, including on fire safety, and this is independently certified by Building Control or an Approved Inspector before buildings are occupied. Where sprinklers are deemed necessary to keep pupils and staff safe, following an assessment of risk at the design stage, or to meet local planning requirements, they should be fitted.</p><p>Following the tragic Grenfell fire, the government has launched a Public Inquiry and an independent review of Building Regulations and Fire Safety. Alongside the rest of Government, we will take forward any relevant recommendations.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-11-03T12:22:15.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777762/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777762/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777762/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Schools: Fire Extinguishers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will make an assessment of the potential merits of making it compulsory for all schools to have sprinklers installed.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","109693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777763","Department for Education","false","2017-11-03","<p>The schools block funding allocation in 2015-16 was £32.2bn for England and £148m for Wandsworth local authority.</p><p>We have now published full detail of the school and high needs national funding formulae, and the impact they will have for every local authority here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-funding-formula-tables-for-schools-and-high-needs" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-funding-formula-tables-for-schools-and-high-needs</a>.</p><p>In 2019-20 England’s schools block allocation would rise to £33.6bn, based on pupil numbers and characteristics from 2017-18. The actual allocation for 2019-20 will be adjusted to take account of more recent pupil number and characteristic data. On the same basis, Wandsworth would receive £155m and Tooting would receive £61.2m. We do not allocate funding on a regional basis so we do not calculate statistics for the Greater London Authority.</p><p>The independent Institute for Fiscal Studies have said, the additional £1.3 billion we are investing in schools funding means that overall funding per pupil across the country will now be maintained in real terms up to 2020. We do not calculate real terms funding estimates at a local level.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-11-03T12:05:36.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777763/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777763/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777763/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the change will be in funding to schools from baseline block funding allocation 2015-16 to academic year 2019-20 of the implementation of the National Funding Formula in (a) Tooting constituency, (b) Wandsworth Borough Council, (c) Greater London Authority and (d) the UK in (i) nominal and (ii) real terms.","false","Biography information for Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","Tooting","Dr Rosena Allin-Khan","109698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777764","Department for Education","false","2017-11-01","<p>The Government will publish a careers strategy in the autumn. The strategy will have a clear focus on social mobility and will include proposals to improve the quality and coverage of careers advice in schools and colleges and give people the information they need to access training throughout their working lives.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2017-11-01T20:40:54.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777764/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777764/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777764/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Schools: Vocational Guidance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when her Department plans to launch its careers strategy.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","109699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777765","Department for Education","false","2017-11-01","<p>We want to ensure that high quality apprenticeships are as accessible as possible to all people from all backgrounds.</p><p> </p><p>Apprenticeships already disproportionately benefit people from lower socio-economic backgrounds with apprentices more likely to come from disadvantaged backgrounds - compared to the population as a whole, 25 per cent of apprentices live in the most disadvantaged fifth of areas.</p><p> </p><p>Our apprenticeship funding policy supports individuals from disadvantaged areas by providing a cash payment to training providers when they train apprentices living in the top 27% of deprived areas.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","109597","2017-11-01T20:39:02.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777765/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777765/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777765/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Apprentices: Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps her Department plans to take to increase apprenticeship enrolment among people from lower-income backgrounds.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","109701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777766","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>As of 31 August, over 216,000 30 hours eligibility codes have been issued for the Autumn term. Whilst the majority of parents applied with no issue, some parents experienced difficulties. HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) are working with National Savings &amp; Investments (and their supplier Atos) to make a range of improvements to the childcare service. The department maintains continuous contact with HMRC and are involved in key discussions.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC put in place arrangements to ensure parents were able to access a place in the Autumn term. For example, they provided 30 hours free childcare codes manually to all parents who reported experiencing difficulties applying through the digital route. The department then encouraged all local authorities to fund 30 hours places for the autumn term where the parent applied on 31 August or before, but received their code after the deadline.</p><p>We are committed to working with colleagues to ensure we continue to improve the customer experience as we deliver this important programme nationally.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-30T16:40:03.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777766/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777766/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777766/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Oral contribution of the Minister of State for Education of 18 July 2017, Official Report, column 713, what discussions her Department has had with HM Revenue and Customs to resolve the issues identified with the digital childcare service; and what progress her Department has made on steps identified in those discussions to resolve those issues.","false","Biography information for Heidi Allen","South Cambridgeshire","Heidi Allen","109758"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777767","Department for Education","false","2017-10-31","<p>There are currently 49 open university technical colleges (UTCs). Since 2010, seven UTCs have closed. These are:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Name of UTC</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Date of closure</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Black Country UTC</p></td><td><p>August 2015</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Hackney UTC</p></td><td><p>August 2015</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Central Bedfordshire UTC</p></td><td><p>August 2016</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Daventry UTC</p></td><td><p>August 2017</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Greater Manchester Sustainable Engineering UTC</p></td><td><p>August 2017</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Tottenham UTC</p></td><td><p>August 2017</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>UTC Lancashire</p></td><td><p>August 2017</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The primary objective of the Department when making a decision to close a school is to ensure the best possible educational outcomes for pupils and to secure value for money for the taxpayer. The Department’s published accounts include the capital and revenue spending for any UTCs which has closed.</p><p> </p><p>Capital funding for open free schools, UTCs and studio schools where costs have been finalised is published on gov.uk at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/capital-funding-for-open-free-schools" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/capital-funding-for-open-free-schools</a>. The final capital costs for all UTCs that have closed since 2010 have not yet been published but are due to be included in the next publication round in coming months.</p><p> </p><p>Schools block funding allocations are published on gov.uk. The link for post 16 data is found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/16-to-19-education-funding-allocations" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/guidance/16-to-19-education-funding-allocations</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Pupil premium: allocations and conditions of grant are published on gov.uk at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/pupil-premium-information-for-schools-and-alternative-provision-settings" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/guidance/pupil-premium-information-for-schools-and-alternative-provision-settings</a>.</p><p> </p><p>We are in the process of making a routine update to the data that we hold on pre and post-opening grant allocations for free schools, UTCs and Studio Schools, following the opening of new schools, in September. We will be publishing the latest data on gov.uk, in the coming weeks.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-31T13:27:45.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777767/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777767/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777767/answer","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777767/answer/previousversion/18739","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","University Technical Colleges: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much (a) revenue and (b) capital spending was allocated from the public purse to each university technical college that has closed since 2010.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","109764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777768","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>The careers strategy will include proposals to improve the quality and coverage of careers advice in schools.</p><p> </p><p>These proposals will be informed by evidence regarding what works. The Gatsby benchmarks are based on the best national and international research and define excellence in careers provision. A two year pilot of the Gatsby benchmarks in the North East has demonstrated that significant improvements can be made.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-30T17:46:44.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777768/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777768/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777768/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Schools: Vocational Guidance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 19 October 2017 to Question 107822, what steps she is taking to ensure that schools meet more than two Gatsby benchmarks of good practice in careers education, information, advice and guidance.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","109667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777769","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>The apprenticeship ambassadors have been selected for their enthusiasm and ability to drive support for the apprenticeship programme. The Apprenticeship Ambassadors that have been appointed will work with all MPs in England to champion the opportunities and benefits that apprenticeships can offer and promote the programme to employers, young people, schools and other key partners.</p><p> </p><p>If any further MP Apprenticeship Ambassadors are to be appointed, MPs from all parties will be considered in light of their support for the apprenticeships programme. Future appointments will be announced as and when they are made.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-30T17:48:25.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777769/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777769/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777769/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether she plans to appoint further ambassadors for the apprentice ambassador programme on a cross-party basis.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","109668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777770","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>I refer the hon. Member for Blackpool South to the answer I gave on 24 October 2017 to PQ 108669:</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-10-19/108669/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-10-19/108669/</a>.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2017-10-30T16:41:48.933Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777770/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777770/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777770/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Education: Reviews","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when she plans to announce further details of the review of tertiary education.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","109669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777771","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>This is a matter for Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector, Amanda Spielman. I have asked her to write to the hon. Member for Ashton-under-Lyne (Angela Rayner). A copy of her reply will be placed in the libraries of the House.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-10-30T17:11:26.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777771/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777771/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777771/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Ofsted: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many inspectors are employed by Ofsted in each region of England.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","109672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777772","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>The recently published Evaluation of the FE Reform Programme report provides a number of key findings. In particular, 83% of providers either reported an increase in the numbers of disadvantaged learners, or had not noticed any fall in the numbers, as a consequence of those reforms to Further Education.</p><p> </p><p>The department will continue to ensure that there are clear communications about the benefits of study supported by Advanced Learner Loans, so that those from all backgrounds can access such loans to enhance their career prospects.</p><p> </p><p>The Advanced Learner Loans Bursary Fund provides additional support to loan-funded learners that require assistance in meeting costs associated with their study, such as childcare, travel, books and equipment, plus any learning support needs.</p><p> </p><p>The latest evaluation of Advanced Learner Loans, commencing in November, will look at the impact of the extension to those aged 19-23 and to Level 5 and Level 6. It will provide the Department with further evidence on how the offer supports adults from different backgrounds.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-30T17:45:16.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777772/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777772/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777772/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment she has made of the findings of the evaluation of the further education reform programme 2015 research report commissioned, by her Department, on the effect of student loans on learners from disadvantaged backgrounds.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","109670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777773","Department for Education","false","2017-11-03","<p>The National Audit Office published an estimate of the cost pressures faced by schools between 2015-16 and 2019-20 in December 2016, available at: <a href="https://www.nao.org.uk/report/financial-sustainability-in-schools/" target="_blank">https://www.nao.org.uk/report/financial-sustainability-in-schools/</a>.</p><p> </p><p>On 17 July 2017, my Rt Hon. Friend, the Secretary of State, announced that the Department will provide an additional £1.3 billion for schools and high needs across 2018-19 and 2019-20, on top of the spending plans considered in the NAO report. Core funding for schools will rise from almost £41 billion in 2017-18 to £42.4 billion in 2018-19, and £43.5 billion in 2019‑20. This represents an increase of over 6%. As the Institute for Fiscal Studies has confirmed, this means that overall funding for schools and high needs will be maintained in real terms per pupil over the next two years.</p><p> </p><p>We will be publishing an updated assessment of cost pressures for schools, taking account of this additional funding, which will include consideration of the withdrawal of the Education Services Grant and the introduction of the apprenticeship levy, and any planned changes to national insurance. Schools are funded to meet the costs of business rates on the basis of actual charges.<strong><br> </strong></p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-11-03T16:51:19.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777773/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777773/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777773/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Schools: Oxfordshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment her Department has made of the effect on the budgets of Oxfordshire primary and secondary schools of (a) changes to business rates, (b) the apprenticeship levy, (c) changes to national insurance contributions and (d) the withdrawal of the education services grant.","false","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","109769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777774","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>The information is not readily available and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-10-30T17:49:27.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777774/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777774/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777774/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Schools: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of children live within three miles of three outstanding schools in each local authority in England.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","109742"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777775","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>We announced within the Childhood Obesity Plan in August 2016 that we would launch a breakfast club programme using funds solely from the Soft Drinks Industry Levy.</p><p>We published an invitation to tender on the 16 October 2017 indicating that we are investing £26 million from the levy over the next three years to expand breakfast club provision.</p><p> </p><p>We have also invested £100 million from the Soft Drinks Industry Levy in the healthy pupils capital fund to facilitate an improvement in children’s physical and mental health by increasing and improving access to and use of relevant facilities, such as kitchens, dining facilities, changing rooms and sports facilities.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","109689","2017-10-30T17:14:04.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777775/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777775/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777775/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Breakfast Clubs: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to her Oral Statement of 17 July 2017, Official Report, columns 563 to 566, on schools update, whether the £10 million ringfenced from the soft drinks industry levy revenue to provide breakfast clubs will be affected by changes to the funding levels available through the healthy pupils capital budget.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","109743"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777776","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>We are considering a range of approaches to increasing the number of graduates employed in the early years sector, but work is still underway. We will engage the sector in exploring ways to target support where it is most needed. We continue to support graduates into the sector through our funding of the Early Years Initial Teacher Training programme, including bursaries and employer incentives.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-30T16:37:41.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777776/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777776/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777776/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Pre-school Education: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the Early Years Workforce Strategy, published in march 2017, what progress her Department has made on plans to conduct a feasibility study on the development of a programme to grow the graduate workforce in Opportunity areas.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","109626"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777777","Department for Education","false","2017-10-31","<p>There are currently 390 open free schools. Since 2010, eight free schools have closed. These are:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Name of free school</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Date of closure</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Discovery New School</p></td><td><p>April 2014</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>The Durham Free School</p></td><td><p>March 2015</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Dawes Lane Academy</p></td><td><p>August 2015</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Stockport Technical School</p></td><td><p>August 2015</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>St Michael’s Secondary School</p></td><td><p>August 2016</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Southwark Free School</p></td><td><p>February 2017</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Collective Spirit</p></td><td><p>August 2017</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bolton Wanderers</p></td><td><p>August 2017</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The primary objective of the Department when making a decision to close a school is to ensure the best possible educational outcomes for pupils and to secure value for money for the taxpayer. The Department’s published accounts include the capital and revenue spending for any free schools which has closed.</p><p> </p><p>Capital funding for open free schools, university technical colleges and studio schools, where costs have been finalised, is published on gov.uk at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/capital-funding-for-open-free-schools" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/capital-funding-for-open-free-schools</a>. The final capital costs for all free schools that have closed since 2010 have not yet been published but are due to be included in the next publication round in coming months.</p><p> </p><p>Schools block funding allocations are published on gov.uk. The link for pre 16 is found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/schools-block-funding-allocations" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/schools-block-funding-allocations</a> and post 16 data is found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/16-to-19-education-funding-allocations" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/guidance/16-to-19-education-funding-allocations</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Pupil premium: allocations and conditions of grant are published on gov.uk found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/pupil-premium-information-for-schools-and-alternative-provision-settings" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/guidance/pupil-premium-information-for-schools-and-alternative-provision-settings</a>.</p><p> </p><p>We are in the process of making a routine update to the data that we hold on pre and post-opening grant allocations for free schools, UTCs and Studio Schools, following the opening of new schools, in September. We will be publishing the latest data on gov.uk, in the coming weeks.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-31T13:33:16.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777777/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777777/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777777/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Free Schools: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, which free schools have closed since 2010; and how much (a) revenue and (b) capital expenditure was disbursed on each of those schools.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","109747"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777778","Department for Education","false","2017-11-03","<p>Data on numbers of apprenticeship starts by age, region, local authority and constituency is available through the Further Education Data library tables: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships</a>. We do not hold data on the number of starts by household income.</p><p> </p><p>Data on the number of levy paying employers that are registered on the apprenticeship service, and can therefore access and benefit from levy funds, is available (as reported to the end of August 2017) here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/apprenticeship-service-registrations-and-commitments-august-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/apprenticeship-service-registrations-and-commitments-august-2017</a>. These statistics are published on a monthly basis. We do not hold this data for non-levy paying employers as their apprenticeship training is funded via contracts with training providers.</p><p> </p><p>Recent data show that over 90 per cent of apprentices currently go into work or further training at the end of their apprenticeship, the majority of these with the same employer.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","109596 ; 109598","2017-11-03T10:20:55.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777778/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777778/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777778/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate she has made of the number of apprenticeships at companies benefiting from the apprenticeship levy by (a) household income, (b) region and (c) age.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","109594"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777779","Department for Education","false","2017-11-03","<p>Ofsted currently makes a valuable contribution to the Department’s understanding of multi academy trust (MAT) performance through focused inspections of schools within the same MAT.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is also working with Ofsted to develop new approaches to better scrutinise MATs. We will publish details in due course.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-11-03T12:59:38.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777779/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777779/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777779/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Academies: Inspections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether she plans to allow Ofsted to inspect multi-academy trusts.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","109665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777780","Department for Education","false","2017-11-03","<p>The Network of Excellence for Computer Science Teaching is a Department funded programme which provides high-quality continuing professional development to existing teachers in England.</p><p>This programme is contracted to the British Computing Society who have members and local branches across the whole of the UK. Through its management of Computing At Schools, a network of local hubs for computing science teachers across the UK, the British Computing Society ensures that the Network of Excellence is part of a collaborative UK wide network. The Network of Excellence responds to local needs through collaboration with wider programmes such as the STEM learning centre in York, the London mayor’s digital programmes, the Raspberry Pi Foundation and Apps for Good.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-11-03T12:55:30.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777780/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777780/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777780/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","ICT: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps the Government is taking to enhance collaboration between the (a) Network of Teaching Excellence in Computer Science and (b) other programmes in England and equivalent computing teacher support programmes in the devolved nations.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","109646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777781","Department for Education","false","2017-11-03","<p>The Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA) does not intend to publish the report. As part of routine business, the ESFA carried out a fact finding review in August 2016 at Collective Spirit Free School. In accordance with published policy, these routine reports are not released.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-11-03T14:57:44.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777781/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777781/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777781/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Collective Spirit Free School Oldham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will take steps to publish the internal audit reports carried out by the Education and Skills Funding Agency on the Collective Spirit Free School, Oldham.","false","Biography information for Jim McMahon","Oldham West and Royton","Jim McMahon","109586"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777782","Department for Education","false","2017-11-03","<p>Data on numbers of apprenticeship starts by age, region, local authority and constituency is available through the Further Education Data library tables: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships</a>. We do not hold data on the number of starts by household income.</p><p> </p><p>Data on the number of levy paying employers that are registered on the apprenticeship service, and can therefore access and benefit from levy funds, is available (as reported to the end of August 2017) here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/apprenticeship-service-registrations-and-commitments-august-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/apprenticeship-service-registrations-and-commitments-august-2017</a>. These statistics are published on a monthly basis. We do not hold this data for non-levy paying employers as their apprenticeship training is funded via contracts with training providers.</p><p> </p><p>Recent data show that over 90 per cent of apprentices currently go into work or further training at the end of their apprenticeship, the majority of these with the same employer.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","109594 ; 109598","2017-11-03T10:20:55.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777782/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777782/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777782/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate her Department has made of the number of employers that benefit from the apprenticeship levy; and how many apprentices have remained at their place of employment after their apprenticeship has concluded.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","109596"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777783","Department for Education","false","2017-11-01","<p>We want to ensure that high quality apprenticeships are as accessible as possible to all people from all backgrounds.</p><p> </p><p>Apprenticeships already disproportionately benefit people from lower socio-economic backgrounds with apprentices more likely to come from disadvantaged backgrounds - compared to the population as a whole, 25 per cent of apprentices live in the most disadvantaged fifth of areas.</p><p> </p><p>Our apprenticeship funding policy supports individuals from disadvantaged areas by providing a cash payment to training providers when they train apprentices living in the top 27% of deprived areas.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","109701","2017-11-01T20:39:03.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777783/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777783/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777783/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that the apprenticeship levy increases social mobility.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","109597"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777784","Department for Education","false","2017-11-03","<p>Data on numbers of apprenticeship starts by age, region, local authority and constituency is available through the Further Education Data library tables: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships</a>. We do not hold data on the number of starts by household income.</p><p> </p><p>Data on the number of levy paying employers that are registered on the apprenticeship service, and can therefore access and benefit from levy funds, is available (as reported to the end of August 2017) here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/apprenticeship-service-registrations-and-commitments-august-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/apprenticeship-service-registrations-and-commitments-august-2017</a>. These statistics are published on a monthly basis. We do not hold this data for non-levy paying employers as their apprenticeship training is funded via contracts with training providers.</p><p> </p><p>Recent data show that over 90 per cent of apprentices currently go into work or further training at the end of their apprenticeship, the majority of these with the same employer.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","109594 ; 109596","2017-11-03T10:20:55.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777784/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777784/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777784/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-25","Apprentices: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate her Department has made of the number of apprentices who have secured apprenticeships at a company benefiting from the apprenticeship levy in (a) Leigh, (b) Wigan and (c) Greater Manchester.","false"