"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777828","Department of Health","false","2017-11-02","<p>The Department has not made estimates of the numbers of additional informal carers in 2020 or 2040. The Department expects to explore this area further as part of wider work on the sustainability of adult social care.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2017-11-02T11:45:53.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777828/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777828/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777828/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-25","Carers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate his Department has made of the number of additional unpaid carers there will be by (a) 2020 and (b) 2040.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","109694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777829","Department of Health","false","2017-10-30","<p>NHS England has advised that the outcome of this pilot has been fed into the commissioning plan agreed within Yorkshire and the Humber to support increased access in identified areas. Bradford South is one of those within this group. Work is ongoing to consider how this will be implemented in this area in 2018/19.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-10-30T15:42:49.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777829/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777829/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777829/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-25","Dental Services: Bradford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the outcome of the recent pilot in Bradford and its surrounding area on improving NHS dental availability.","false","Biography information for Judith Cummins","Bradford South","Judith Cummins","109686"
