"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777949","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-30","<p>The Taylor Review of Modern Working Practices was a large and comprehensive report. We are now taking the time the report deserves to consider the recommendations before the Government responds.</p><p> </p><p>We will publish the Government response by the end of the year.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-30T14:37:43.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777949/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777949/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777949/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-25","Modern Working Practices Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he plans to publish his response to the Taylor Review of modern working practices, published in July 2017, before the November 2017 recess.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","109625"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777950","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-30","<p>Like all departments, BEIS is planning for a number of EU Exit scenarios to make sure we are ready on Day 1.</p><p>Over £250m of additional funding has been approved across a number of departments in 2017/18 to prepare for Brexit.</p><p>BEIS has received additional funding this year to meet new pressures arising from Brexit preparations.</p><p>Additional funding received from the reserve for 2017/8 will be set out at Supplementary Estimates.</p><p>The costs of EU Exit in 2018-19 will be affected by negotiations over the coming months.</p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-30T17:21:14.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777950/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777950/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777950/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-25","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what funding his Department has set aside for contingencies relating to the UK leaving the EU in the (a) 2017-18 and (b) 2018-19 financial years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","109782"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777951","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-10-30","<p>Like all departments, BEIS is planning for a number of EU Exit scenarios to make sure we are ready on Day 1.</p><p>Over £250m of additional funding has been approved across a number of departments in 2017/18 to prepare for Brexit.</p><p>BEIS has received additional funding this year to meet new pressures arising from Brexit preparations.</p><p>Additional funding received from the reserve for 2017/8 will be set out at Supplementary Estimates.</p><p>The costs of EU Exit in 2018-19 will be affected by negotiations over the coming months.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2017-10-30T17:21:55.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777951/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777951/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777951/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-10-25","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what contingency funding his Department has allocated in relation to the Government's negotiations on the UK leaving the EU for the (a) 2017-18, (b) 2018-19 and (c) 2019-20 financial years.","false","Biography information for Stella Creasy","Walthamstow","Stella Creasy","109780"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777952","Department for International Trade","false","2017-10-30","<p>Like all departments, the Department of International Trade (DIT) is planning for a number of scenarios to make sure we are ready on Day 1 of EU Exit.</p><p>Over £250m of additional funding has been approved across a number of departments in 2017/18 to prepare for Brexit.</p><p>DIT has received additional funding this year, and has reprioritised to meet new pressures arising from Brexit preparations.</p><p>Additional funding received from the reserve for 2017/8 will be set out at Supplementary Estimates.</p><p>The costs of EU Exit in 2018-19 will be affected by negotiations over the coming months.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-10-30T17:48:31.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777952/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777952/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777952/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-10-25","Department for International Trade: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what funding his Department has set aside for contingencies relating to the UK leaving the EU in the (a) current and (b) 2018-19 financial year.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","109785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777953","Department for International Trade","false","2017-10-30","<p>The Government is carrying out an ongoing programme of comprehensive analytical work that will inform our negotiating position with the EU, to define our deep and special partnership with the EU and inform our understanding of how EU exit will affect the UK’s domestic policies and frameworks.</p><p>The Department for International Trade is working with officials across government, in close coordination with the Department for Exiting the European Union, to ensure the delivery of a holistic programme of analysis across government.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-10-30T16:59:27.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777953/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777953/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777953/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-10-25","Department for International Trade: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether his Department was consulted by the Department for Exiting the European Union on the economic impact assessments conducted for the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","109548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777954","Department for International Trade","false","2017-11-03","<p>We take very seriously the allegations made by Amnesty International on the role of a UK company in the sale of arms to South Sudan. We have consistently called for a UN arms embargo to be implemented with immediate effect. Such an embargo would prevent any sale of arms to South Sudan globally.</p><p>The UK Government has not authorised the supply of arms to South Sudan and DIT has not issued any trade or export licences for arms to South Sudan.</p><p>Amnesty International has passed their information to HMRC and it is being assessed.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-11-03T13:20:53.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777954/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777954/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777954/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-10-25","Arms Trade: South Sudan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what information his Department holds on the supply of arms by a British company to the Government of South Sudan; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","109574"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777955","Department for International Trade","false","2017-10-30","<p>In pursuing technical rectification of UK tariff schedules at the World Trade Organization (WTO), we aim to replicate as far as possible our current obligations; this includes commitments under the Information Technology Agreement (ITA) of 1996, and the ITA expansion declaration of 2015.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-10-30T17:38:32.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777955/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777955/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777955/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-10-25","ICT: Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what plans the Government has to bring forward a schedule of commitments on trade in IT equipment to be agreed with new trading partners after the UK leaves the EU; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Angus Brendan MacNeil","Na h-Eileanan an Iar","Angus Brendan MacNeil","109690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777956","Department for International Trade","false","2017-11-03","<p>The dairy sector is an important contributor to food and drink exports with increasing demand internationally for our products. For example, cheese is our 5<sup>th</sup> largest food and drink export and has seen a 26% increase in exports to £292m for the first 6 months of this year. Milk, cream and butter are also seeing increasing demand internationally.</p><p>The Department for International Trade’s food and drink team currently run six high value campaigns targeting China, India, Western Europe, North America, Latin America and the Nordics. The dairy sector is integral to the delivery of these campaigns.</p><p>To recognise the importance of the food and drink sector, the Great British Food Programme has been designed to allow South West food and drink businesses to directly interact with overseas buyers. Since April 2016 DIT South West has helped businesses in the sector win over £19.5m worth of export business across more than 30 markets.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-11-03T13:27:55.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777956/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777956/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777956/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-10-25","Dairy Products: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what assessment he has made of export opportunities in the dairy sector.","false","Biography information for Scott Mann","North Cornwall","Scott Mann","109603"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777957","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-11-02","<p>The Government is working closely with the aviation sector to ensure it continues to be a major success story for the UK economy. Ministers and officials from across Government have met widely with the sector since the referendum, covering the full spectrum of issues affecting the industry.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-11-02T17:04:43.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777957/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777957/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/777957/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-10-25","Aviation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what representations the Government has received from the aviation sector on priorities for its negotiations on the UK leaving the EU; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Henry Smith","Crawley","Henry Smith","109700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776751","Department for Education","false","2017-11-07","<p>The evaluation of Disabled Students’ Allowances (DSA) will address a range of factors relating to the efficacy of support for disabled students, including the effect of recent changes to DSA policy.</p>",,"The Earl of Courtown","HL2416 ; HL2417","2017-11-07T17:48:22.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776751/answer","Biography information for The Earl of Courtown","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776751/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776751/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Disabled Students' Allowances","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether the evaluation of Disabled Students' Allowances will include consideration of the levels of information provided by higher education providers to students claiming those allowances about the respective responsibilities of those institutions and students.","false","Biography information for Lord Addington",,"Lord Addington","HL2415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776752","Department for Education","false","2017-11-07","<p>The evaluation of Disabled Students’ Allowances (DSA) will address a range of factors relating to the efficacy of support for disabled students, including the effect of recent changes to DSA policy.</p>",,"The Earl of Courtown","HL2415 ; HL2417","2017-11-07T17:48:22.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776752/answer","Biography information for The Earl of Courtown","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776752/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776752/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Disabled Students' Allowances","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether the evaluation of Disabled Students' Allowances will include consideration of the benefits of issuing a guide to higher education providers about their responsibilities in relation to students claiming those allowances who fall into bands 1 and 2.","false","Biography information for Lord Addington",,"Lord Addington","HL2416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776753","Department for Education","false","2017-11-07","<p>The evaluation of Disabled Students’ Allowances (DSA) will address a range of factors relating to the efficacy of support for disabled students, including the effect of recent changes to DSA policy.</p>",,"The Earl of Courtown","HL2415 ; HL2416","2017-11-07T17:48:22.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776753/answer","Biography information for The Earl of Courtown","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776753/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776753/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Disabled Students' Allowances","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether the evaluation of Disabled Students' Allowances will include consideration of the need for third party advisers to have clarity of information about the respective responsibilities of higher education providers and claimants of those allowances.","false","Biography information for Lord Addington",,"Lord Addington","HL2417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776754","Department for International Development","false","2017-10-31","<p>The UK is the largest bilateral donor to the Rohingya refugee crisis. In addition to the £35m the UK had committed since the start of this crisis, on October 23<sup>rd</sup> the UK announced a further £12m of support, bringing the UK total to £47m. This funding is already delivering important relief on the ground, including providing food to 174,000 people, safe water and sanitation for more than 138,000 people and emergency shelter for over 130,000 people. In addition, emergency nutrition support will reach more than 60,000 children under five and 21,000 pregnant and lactating women, counselling and psychological support will reach over 10,000 women suffering from the trauma of war and over 2,000 survivors of sexual violence, and provide medical assistance for over 50,000 pregnant women.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2017-10-31T17:15:09.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776754/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776754/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776754/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-10-24","Burma: Rohingya","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how much money they have committed to date to assist with the Rohingya refugee crisis.","false","Biography information for Lord Blencathra",,"Lord Blencathra","HL2418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776755","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-02","<p>The UK will be attending the 37th meeting of the Standing Committee of the Bern Convention. We are currently agreeing who the UK representatives will be.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We have recently received the agenda papers and are currently agreeing the UK position.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble","HL2420","2017-11-02T13:01:15.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776755/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776755/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776755/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-24","Convention on the Conservation of European Wildlife and Natural Habitats","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether the UK will be represented at the 37th meeting of the Standing Committee of the Bern Convention in Strasbourg in December; and if so whom the UK representative will be.","false","Biography information for Lord Blencathra",,"Lord Blencathra","HL2419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776756","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-02","<p>The UK will be attending the 37th meeting of the Standing Committee of the Bern Convention. We are currently agreeing who the UK representatives will be.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We have recently received the agenda papers and are currently agreeing the UK position.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble","HL2419","2017-11-02T13:01:15.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776756/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776756/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776756/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-24","Convention on the Conservation of European Wildlife and Natural Habitats","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is their position on the items on the agenda for the 37th Standing Committee of the Bern Convention in December.","false","Biography information for Lord Blencathra",,"Lord Blencathra","HL2420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776757","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-07","<p>The UK has so far committed £57 million towards meeting immediate humanitarian needs in the Overseas Territories. The UK has also committed to supporting the governments of the affected Overseas Territories as they carry out their impact and needs assessments and design their longer term recovery plans.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2017-11-07T17:32:47.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776757/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776757/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776757/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-24","Caribbean: Hurricanes and Tornadoes","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government how much money they have committed to date to assist with the recovery of the British Overseas Territories affected by recent hurricanes.","false","Biography information for Lord Blencathra",,"Lord Blencathra","HL2421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776758","Home Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>The Immigration Act 2014 prohibited banks and building societies from opening new current accounts for disqualified persons. The Immigration Act 2016 goes further and prevents existing accounts from being operated by disqualified persons.</p><p> </p><p>There is no risk of discrimination. It is the individual’s immigration status that will decide whether their details are included in the Home Office data shared with banks and building societies. Individuals will only be affected by these measures if they are disqualified persons. Legal migrants who are able to satisfy commercial requirements for opening and operating an account will continue to have access to financial services.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2017-11-06T17:13:40.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776758/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776758/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776758/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-24","Undocumented Migrants: Financial Services","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the impact of (1) the Immigration Act 2014, and (2) the Immigration Act 2016, on the access of BAME communities to financial services.","false","Biography information for Lord Boateng",,"Lord Boateng","HL2422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776759","Home Office","false","2017-11-06","<p>The Government engages with industry regularly to understand how well the Immigration Act 2014 banking measures are working. The Financial Conduct Authority, as the independent financial services regulator, has concluded that banks and building societies are complying with the requirements of the 2014 Act.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is continuing to engage with industry and the Financial Conduct Authority ahead of implementation of the Immigration Act 2016 banking measures to ensure operational preparedness.</p><p> </p><p>These measures are a proportionate tool to deter immigration crime, tackle illegal migration and protect the integrity of the immigration system. They are compliant with the Data Protection Act 1998 and the Human Rights Act 1998.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2017-11-06T17:12:55.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776759/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776759/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776759/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-10-24","Undocumented Migrants: Financial Services","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what discussions they have had with (1) banking regulators, and (2) the Equality and Human Rights Commission, about the application of the provisions of (a) the Immigration Act 2014, and (b) the Immigration Act 2016, by financial service providers.","false","Biography information for Lord Boateng",,"Lord Boateng","HL2423"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776760","Department of Health","false","2017-11-07","<p>Valproate is an effective treatment for epilepsy and bipolar disorder that should only be used in girls and women of childbearing potential if other treatments are ineffective or not tolerated because of the risks in pregnancy. For some women there may be no other treatment option. Due to ongoing concerns about women’s awareness of the risks, the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency has worked with professional bodies, voluntary organisations and patient groups to develop a set of materials to aid communication between health professionals and women and girls. The adequacy of measures taken to date is being evaluated in a Europe-wide review that started in March 2017. An expert working group of the Commission on Human Medicines has been convened to inform the United Kingdom position during the ongoing European Union review and will consider all relevant data on intergenerational effects.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has great sympathy for those families who have been affected by the use of valproate in pregnancy. However, there is currently no proposal to offer compensation for those affected by the use of valproate during pregnancy in the UK. For any child born with a disability, clinical commissioning groups and local authorities, as commissioners of health and social care, must secure services to meet that child’s needs.</p><p> </p><p>Where a child has a very complex health need, they may need additional health support to that which is routinely available from general practitioner practices, hospitals or in the community, called continuing care. Health, social care and education should work together to meet the needs of children and young people with special educational needs.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy","HL2425 ; HL2426","2017-11-07T15:47:34.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776760/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776760/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776760/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-10-24","Pregnancy: Sodium Valproate","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether UK guidance on the use of valproate-based medicines during pregnancy has been reviewed in the light of recent findings on the intergenerational effects of that drug.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ford",,"Baroness Ford","HL2424"
