"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776856","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-30","<p>The eligibility criteria for entry into the British Army do not consider the citizenship status of an individual's parents.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-30T16:05:36.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776856/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776856/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776856/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-24","Army: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the criteria for an EU national applying to join the British Army take account of the applicant's parents having attained UK citizenship.","false","Biography information for Gavin Robinson","Belfast East","Gavin Robinson","109283"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776857","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-01","<p>The 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review committed to growing the Royal Navy for the first time in a generation. The future fleet will include the Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carriers, the first of which is at sea conducting trials; the Type 45 destroyers; the Type 26 frigates, steel for the first of which was cut in July; Type 31e frigates; the next generation Dreadnought submarines; the Astute Class submarines, and five new Offshore Patrol Vessels. In addition, a shipbuilding programme is under way to deliver four Tide Class tankers, the first of which, Royal Fleet Auxiliary TIDESPRING, joins the operational fleet later this year, as well as three new Future Solid Support Ships. We will also increase Naval Service personnel numbers by 400 to 30,600 by 2025.</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-11-01T15:28:40.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776857/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776857/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776857/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-24","Navy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how he defines the term growing Royal Navy.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","109310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776858","Department for International Trade","false","2017-10-30","<p>The DIT Defence and Security Organisation recorded no new orders of defence exports to Iran in 2016 as the sale, supply, transfer or export to Iran, of all military goods and technology as listed in the UK Military List remain banned under the proliferation-related sanctions.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-10-30T12:41:44.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776858/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776858/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776858/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-10-24","Exports: Iran","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, with reference to UK Defence and Security Export Statistics for 2016, how much of the £5.9 billion that the UK exported, based on orders, was paid for by the Government of Iran.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","109243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776859","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-01","<p>Since August 2016, the RAF Typhoon fleet has been supported through the Typhoon Total Availability eNterprise contract (TyTAN). This is based on contracting for availability and provides sufficient spare parts to support the current forward available fleet and operational plan.</p><p> </p><p>Typhoon EJ200 engines continue to be supported by the Partnered Support Operational Phase 3 (PSOP3) availability contract.</p><p> </p><p>The current level of spare parts for the Typhoon fleet remains at a sufficient level to support the TyTAN and PSOP3 contracts and is shown below. The spares inventory will fluctuate over time as availability is proactively managed.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td><p>Quantity</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><p>Typhoon Airframe Inventory Spares</p></td><td><p>12,850</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p>Engines EJ200</p></td><td><p>Uninstalled</p></td><td><p>118</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Installed</p></td><td><p>222</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","109228","2017-11-01T15:22:16.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776859/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776859/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776859/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-24","European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the recommended level of spare parts held by the armed forces for the UK's Typhoon squadrons is.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","109227"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776860","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-01","<p>Since August 2016, the RAF Typhoon fleet has been supported through the Typhoon Total Availability eNterprise contract (TyTAN). This is based on contracting for availability and provides sufficient spare parts to support the current forward available fleet and operational plan.</p><p> </p><p>Typhoon EJ200 engines continue to be supported by the Partnered Support Operational Phase 3 (PSOP3) availability contract.</p><p> </p><p>The current level of spare parts for the Typhoon fleet remains at a sufficient level to support the TyTAN and PSOP3 contracts and is shown below. The spares inventory will fluctuate over time as availability is proactively managed.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><p> </p></td><td><p>Quantity</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><p>Typhoon Airframe Inventory Spares</p></td><td><p>12,850</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p>Engines EJ200</p></td><td><p>Uninstalled</p></td><td><p>118</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Installed</p></td><td><p>222</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","109227","2017-11-01T15:22:16.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776860/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776860/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776860/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-24","European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the level of spare parts held by the armed forces for the UK's Typhoon squadrons was at the latest date for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","109228"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776861","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-01","<p>The cost of spare parts for Typhoon for each financial year (FY) since 2010-11 is shown below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>FY</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£ million</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>35.9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>41.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>45.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>56.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>63.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>63.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>43.4</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-01T15:27:56.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776861/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776861/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776861/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-24","European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much has been spent by his Department and the armed services on Typhoon spare parts in each financial year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","109229"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776862","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-31","<p>Of the 19 staff who attended the naming ceremony for Royal Fleet Auxiliary TIDESURGE on 29 August 2017, 13 were members of the UK Armed Forces and six were Ministry of Defence civilian staff. The date aligned with a routine project meeting.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-10-31T16:09:28.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776862/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776862/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776862/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-24","RFA Tidesurge","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) staff of his Department and (b) members of the UK armed forces were in attendance at the naming ceremony for RFA Tidesurge at DSME Shipyard in Okpo, South Korea on 1 September 2017.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","109312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776863","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-01","<p>The total cost to the Ministry of Defence of transporting the Lady Sponsor, Mrs Woodcock, her husband, the 2nd Sea Lord, Vice-Admiral Jonathan Woodcock and his Military Assistant, to the naming ceremony of Royal Fleet Auxiliary TIDESURGE on 29 August 2017 was £5,488.</p><p>Costs of accommodation and transfers within the Republic of Korea were funded separately under the contract with Daewoo Shipbuilding and Marine Engineering.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-01T15:29:31.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776863/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776863/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776863/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-24","RFA Tidesurge","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the cost to the public purse was of transporting the Lady Sponsor and accompanying guests to South Korea for the naming ceremony for RFA Tidesurge on 1 September 2017.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","109313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776864","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-31","<p>I can confirm that for the period between 14 and 23 October 2017 HMS ST ALBANS was the designated Fleet Ready Escort.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-31T16:00:09.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776864/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776864/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776864/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-24","Navy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the designated Fleet Ready Escort was on each day between 14 and 23 October 2017.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","109314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776865","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-10-31","<p>Ministry of Defence policy on unauthorised encampments is that the Department will always take appropriate action to recover possession of its land.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-10-31T16:10:02.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776865/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776865/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776865/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-24","Travellers: Caravan Sites","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his Department's policy is on tackling unauthorised traveller encampments on his Department's land.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","109323"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776866","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-11-01","<p>The Red Arrows and their support team recently completed a highly successful tour of the Middle East. The table below shows the date of the last display by named country, together with the number of additional personnel from the Department at individual events. The Red Arrows did not conduct any displays in the United Arab Emirates.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Country</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Date of Last Display</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>No. of MOD Personnel in Attendance</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Saudi Arabia</p></td><td><p>11 October 2017</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jordan</p></td><td><p>23 September 2017</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Kuwait</p></td><td><p>28 September 2017</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Qatar</p></td><td><p>30 September 2017</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oman</p></td><td><p>3 October 2017</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bahrain</p></td><td><p>8 October 2017</p></td><td><p>6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>United Arab Emirates</p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td><td><p>Nil</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The cost of the tour was primarily funded from within the Red Arrows flying hours allocation for Financial Year 2017-18. Costings for individual displays are not held in the format requested.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-11-01T15:24:08.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776866/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776866/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776866/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-10-24","Red Arrows","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on which dates the Red Arrows display team last performed in (a) Saudi Arabia, (b) Jordan, (c) Kuwait, (d) Qatar, (e) Oman, (f) Bahrain and (g) the United Arab Emirates; how many personnel from his Department attended each such performance; and what the cost to the public purse was of each such performance.","false","Biography information for Martin Docherty-Hughes","West Dunbartonshire","Martin Docherty-Hughes","109315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776867","Department for Education","false","2017-11-01","<p>I am sorry, but we do not hold data on unfilled vacancies. Employers are responsible for staff recruitment.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-11-01T17:49:49.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776867/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776867/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776867/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Pre-school Education: Vacancies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate her Department has made of the number of unfilled vacancies there are in private and voluntary-run nurseries and pre-schools; and what steps she is taking to ensure that those vacancies are filled.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","109275"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776868","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>The Department regularly meets with teaching unions who represent the views of their members, which include supply teachers. The last meeting my department held to specifically discuss supply teacher working practices was in October 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is aware of concerns about insecure working practices for supply teachers, in particular relating to practices of some supply teacher agencies. The Department is in the planning phase of a new commercial framework for schools that use supply agencies. The Department will discuss these proposals with the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, particularly in relation to the Taylor Review of modern working practices.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","109408","2017-10-30T17:09:40.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776868/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776868/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776868/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Supply Teachers: Conditions of Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when she last met representatives of supply teachers to discuss their concerns about insecure working practices.","false","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","Chipping Barnet","Theresa Villiers","109278"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776869","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>I refer the hon. Member for Warrington North, Helen Jones to the answer I gave on 23 October 2017 to Question 108600:</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=108600" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=108600</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong><br> </strong></p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-30T16:54:46.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776869/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776869/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776869/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many (a) applications and (b) admissions for initial teacher training courses specialising in the education of under-fives there were in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","109286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776870","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>There are two different ways we categorised providers who were willing and able to offer 30 hours in the early rollout evaluation report.</p><p> </p><p>For clarification:</p><ul><li>83% of providers in the four early rollout areas delivering free entitlements (the universal 15 hours for 3 and 4 years old and/or the 15 hours for disadvantaged 2 year olds) were willing and able to deliver 30 hours.</li><li>62% of all registered providers in the four early rollout areas were willing and able to deliver 30 hours. However, it is important to highlight that while providers may be registered to deliver childcare this does not mean they are currently offering childcare or have sufficient number of children to fill the places.</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-30T16:48:05.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776870/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776870/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776870/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 9 October 2017 to Question 105348, on children: day care, what the reasons are for the apparent discrepancy between the proportion of providers cited who were willing and able to offer the extended hours places and the data provided on that proportion in paragraph 3 on page 12 of her Department's paper, Evaluation of Early Rollout of 30 Hours Free Childcare, published on 31 August 2017.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","109254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776871","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>The department is committed to supporting parents access a 30 hours’ place. Local councils have a duty to secure childcare provision free of charge to qualifying children. As of 31 August, over 216,000 codes were issued for the autumn term, with 90% being validated as of 9 October.</p><p>We know that some parents will purchase additional hours and services outside of the free entitlements, and where parents do decide to do this, it is a private matter between them and their chosen provider. But parents must not be required to pay any fee as a condition of taking up a free entitlement place, and must be offered alternative options. The early delivery evaluation reports showed that where additional charges were introduced, this had not deterred parents from taking up a place.</p><p>The department will be commissioning an independent evaluation of the first two terms of delivery of the 30 hours where we will be monitoring the impact of 30 hours, including charging for additional services.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-30T16:53:02.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776871/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776871/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776871/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether she has made an estimate of the number of parents who are unable to access funded hours only places; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","109242"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776872","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>The number of 2-year-olds benefitting from funded early education is published in Table 1 of the ‘Education provision: children under 5 years of age’ statistical first release: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/education-provision-children-under-5-years-of-age-january-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/education-provision-children-under-5-years-of-age-january-2017</a>.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-30T16:49:26.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776872/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776872/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776872/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many two-year olds have received 15 hours free childcare in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Tracy Brabin","Batley and Spen","Tracy Brabin","109295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776873","Department for Education","false","2017-10-30","<p>The number and proportion of 2, 3 and 4-year-olds benefitting from funded early education in maintained nursery schools since 2010 are shown in the table. This is published annually in the ‘Education provision: children under 5 years of age’ statistical first release: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/education-provision-children-under-5-years-of-age-january-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/education-provision-children-under-5-years-of-age-january-2017</a>.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-10-30T16:57:31.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776873/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776873/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776873/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-10-24","Pre-school Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many and what proportion of under-fives received early years education in maintained nursery schools in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","109287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776874","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-01","<p>On 30 September the Secretary of State announced that the Government would increase the maximum penalty for animal cruelty offences from six months’ imprisonment to five years’ imprisonment.</p><p> </p><p>This announcement made clear the government will publish draft legislation for consultation around the turn of the year.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-11-01T15:38:22.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776874/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776874/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776874/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-24","Animal Welfare: Sentencing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what the timetable is for the introduction of legislative proposals to increase the maximum sentence for animal cruelty offences to five years imprisonment.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","109235"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776875","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-10-31","<p>Established guidance exists on how to help our native bat species including the provision of bat boxes to provide bats with alternative resting places or to encourage bats into areas where there are few existing suitable roost sites. Further guidance can be accessed through the Bat Conservation Trust: <a href="http://www.bats.org.uk" target="_blank">www.bats.org.uk</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Wildlife boxes (for bats and certain bird species including barn owls) can also be funded through the Countryside Stewardship scheme on eligible land where it would be beneficial for the species.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-10-31T15:34:05.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776875/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776875/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776875/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-24","Bats and Owls: Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans he has to encourage landowners to erect owl and bat boxes on their land; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","109264"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776876","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-10-30","<p>The information requested is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-10-30T16:30:48.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776876/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776876/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776876/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-24","National Parks: EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much funding each national park in England has received in each of the last five financial years from the European Commission and its programmes and agencies.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","109222"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776877","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-01","<p>When the UK leaves the EU on 29 March 2019, we will be leaving the Common Fisheries Policy. The UK will become an independent Coastal State and will be fully responsible, under international law, for control of our Exclusive Economic Zone and for management of fisheries resources within it. We will also have obligations to cooperate with the EU and other coastal states to manage shared stocks.</p><p> </p><p>Decisions on the precise rules that will apply to the area between the territorial sea and the Exclusive Economic Zone have yet to be determined. However, the Government is clear that we want to be a responsible Coastal State and to have a cooperative relationship with the EU and other Coastal States to ensure the sustainable management of fish stocks.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-11-01T12:15:35.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776877/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776877/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776877/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-24","Fisheries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how UK fisheries will be managed after 30 March 2019; whether UK fisheries will be managed out to the Exclusive Economic Zone median line; and whether the UK will apply different rules to the area between the territorial sea and the Exclusive Economic Zone.","false","Biography information for Scott Mann","North Cornwall","Scott Mann","109211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776878","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-01","<p>The UK has been working constructively with other EU Member States on the implementation of the EU landing obligation, or discard ban. The discard ban is being phased in from 2015 to 2019, and the Government will continue to make sure that interests of UK fisheries and fleets are reflected in each new set of rules that are being introduced annually up until 1 January 2019.</p><p> </p><p>The Government remains committed to ending the wasteful practice of discarding fish after we leave the EU.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-11-01T15:54:31.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776878/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776878/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776878/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-24","Fisheries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans he has to stop the dumping of dead fish in UK waters after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Scott Mann","North Cornwall","Scott Mann","109212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776879","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-11-01","<p>Seventy nine local authorities in the UK provide kerbside collection of mixed plastic film; 70 of these are in England.</p><p> </p><p>Information is not held on the proportion of plastic film recycled. From information reported to Defra on local authority collected waste in England in 2015/16, a total of around 7,100 tonnes of low density polyethylene (LDPE) was recycled. LDPE includes plastic film as well as carrier bags and bin liners. We are not able to readily extract the totals for previous years.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-11-01T15:11:53.937Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776879/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776879/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776879/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-10-24","Packaging: Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 19 October 2017 to Question 107602, on packaging, how many local authorities provide roadside collection of plastic wrap; how many tonnes of plastic wrap has been recycled in each of the last five years; and what proportion of plastic wrap used in the UK was recycled in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Tonia Antoniazzi","Gower","Tonia Antoniazzi","109317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776880","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-10-30","<p>The UK is committed to the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty. While we cannot predict when other States will take the decisions necessary to ratify the Treaty, we will continue to press all states who have not yet ratified it, including the US, to do so. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office Minister for Asia made a statement pressing for the entry into force and universalisation of the Treaty at the Conference on Facilitating the Entry Into Force on 20 September 2017. More recently, during the current 72nd Session of the UN General Assembly, the UK co-sponsored a resolution pursuing these goals for the Treaty.</p><p>The UK is a strong supporter of the Preparatory Commission for the Comprehensive Nuclear Test Ban Treaty Organization (CTBTO). We are one of the leading players in the design, maintenance and development of the Treaty's Verification regime. We also contribute funding and extensive UK expertise to the CTBTO, as well as contributions-in-kind for exercises.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-10-30T16:18:39.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776880/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776880/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776880/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-24","Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the outcome of the Conference on Facilitating the Entry Into Force of the Comprehensive Nuclear Test Ban Treaty held on 20 September 2017.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","109335"
