"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776942","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-11-01","<p>According to official statistics released by the Office for National Statistics on 29 September 2017, total direct investment in the UK from abroad stood at £1.493 trillion in the second quarter of 2017. This is the highest level on record.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-11-01T15:15:42.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776942/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776942/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776942/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-10-24","Foreign Investment in UK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to his oral contribution of 17 October 2017, Official Report, column 744, on EU Exit negotiations, what the evidential basis is for his statement that UK inward investment is at record levels in the first half of 2017.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","109265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776943","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-11-01","<p>All Government departments are bound by legal requirements concerning the right to work in the UK and, in addition, the Civil Service Nationality Rules. Evidence of nationality is checked at the point of recruitment into the Civil Service as part of wider pre-employment checks, but there is no requirement on departments to retain this information beyond the point at which it has served its purpose.</p><p>The Department does not hold a month by month breakdown for the period requested.</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-11-01T15:12:20.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776943/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776943/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776943/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-10-24","Department for Exiting the European Union: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many non-British EU nationals have been employed by his Department in each month since it was established.","false","Biography information for Damien Moore","Southport","Damien Moore","109273"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776944","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-11-06","<p>It is Government policy that we will not be a member of the Single Market after the date of our exit from the EU. The United Kingdom is a party to the EEA agreement only in its capacity as an EU member state, so on exit day the EEA agreement will cease to operate in respect of the UK.</p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2017-11-06T16:16:16.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776944/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776944/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776944/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-10-24","UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, pursuant to the Answer of 17 October 2017 to Question 106266, on UK membership of the EU, by whom has such agreement been made that when the UK leaves the EU there is automaticity about the European Economic Area Agreement no longer operating in respect of the UK.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","109234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776945","Cabinet Office","false","2017-11-16","<p>In October 2015 the Government published guidance on departments’ use of telephone prefixes and freephone numbers which can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/470411/20151006_Customer_phone_lines_draft_guidance_October_2015.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/470411/20151006_Customer_phone_lines_draft_guidance_October_2015.pdf</a></p><p>Departments are responsible and accountable for their choice of number prefix, supported by an appropriate numbering policy position. Where appropriate, departments must justify exceptions to the guidance. Information regarding Departments’ use freephone numbers is not held centrally. Departments should be contacted directly regarding this.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-11-16T15:58:30.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776945/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776945/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776945/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-24","Government Departments: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which government departments have freephone numbers for public use.","false","Biography information for Ben Lake","Ceredigion","Ben Lake","109359"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776946","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-01","<p>It is the longstanding policy of the Government not to comment on intelligence matters.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-11-01T17:31:21.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776946/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776946/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776946/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-24","Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to the letter of 15 September 2017 from the Investigatory Powers Commissioner's Office summarising the findings of the 2017 BPD Audit, for how long data gathered from social media services is held by GCHQ before being deleted; and how large the bulk dataset holding that data is.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","109364"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776947","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-11-02","<p>It is the longstanding policy of the Government not to comment on intelligence matters.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-11-02T15:30:57.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776947/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776947/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776947/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-10-24","GCHQ","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to the letter of 15 September 2017 from the Investigatory Powers Commissioner's Office summarising the findings of the 2017 BPD Audit, what methods are used by GCHQ to collect data from social media services; and whether GCHQ collects metadata and content from social media services.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","109365"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776948","Cabinet Office","false","2017-10-30","<p>I refer you to the answers previously given to the Members for Oldham West and Royton and Linlithgow and East Falkirk, PQ1118 answered on 3<sup>rd</sup> July 2017. There are no plans to introduce automatic registration, as it contradicts the principles underpinning Individual Electoral Registration. Making an application to register to vote is the right of individuals and can be done easily online, in as little as three minutes, as well as using the traditional paper form, if people prefer. The 2017 UK parliamentary general election was fought on the largest ever register, according to initial estimates.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","109372 ; 109373","2017-10-30T15:41:01.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776948/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776948/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/776948/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-10-24","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will bring forward proposals for automatic voter registration.","false","Biography information for Chris Elmore","Ogmore","Chris Elmore","109371"
